	   <tr><td colspan=2>These are, as listed, all/all. Therefore any class can use them :P<br><br>However as to your class argument about &quot;whimpy, crying monks&quot;, Here is why this might be considered a monk item (reasons, I'm not saying it is, although I'd love a pair for mine).<br><br>1) These are probably up there on the list, if not the best boots in the game. That is why any melee, monk and sk's included, would want them.<br><br>2) The stats are incredible. For ay melee or hybrid. I think, given a raid, the mana on these would probably be discounted for who they go to, because 35 mana won't do very much at this level (yeah every little bit helps - but if you can get these, go get a Noct blade, you'll get more mana from it).<br><br>3) For Monks, these undoubtedly stand as the best boots in the game. The only other boots that compare, and not well, are Barbed Dragonscale Boots (ac19 sta9 hp30 - weight 2.5). After that, depending if you want ac or stats, you could either a) get footpads of the tiger (ac6 str10 and more), b) get kael booties for extra ac (if you're even allied with kael, cause thurg monk armor is mostly bad), or c) get some reinforced acrylia and deal with your pain.<br><br>Also - please don't go around calling monks whimpy criers because when we see a low weight item we say, &quot;Ooh! A lightweight item good for monks!&quot; (yeah yeah, abbv. &quot;Monk item!&quot;). The reason for this is because you have probably not considered the difficulty we go through with a weight restriction on us. Weapons get heavy. Good armor (barbed dragonscale boots, acrylia reinforced :P) is sometimes heavy. And when we cross that little wieght limit, our ac starts going DOWN. My monk is now almost 47 - and I worry constantly about going over the limit while trying to improve my armor at the same time. I can carry 17 stone until level 51 - when I get to cary 18.<br><br>My advice to you: try getting a monk, with decently good ac, weaps etc. to a mid-high level - it's difficult to stay under that weight limit, and if you experience what we go through, you might appreciate our viewpoint more.<br><br>Sorry for the long post :D<br>&nbsp;<br>Bubuo Blizzardfists<br>&lt;Addicted Elite&gt;<br>51 Iksar Monk, E'ci</td></tr>
